---

# 🎯 Today's Goal

By the end of today, you'll know:

* What technology we'll use
* Why we chose it
* What each technology is responsible for

Think of this as selecting the building materials before constructing a house.

---

# Our Technology Stack

```text
Flutter
      │
FastAPI
      │
PostgreSQL
      │
AWS S3
      │
Google Cloud Vision OCR
      │
OpenAI API
```

Every tool has one specific responsibility.

---

# 1. Flutter (Mobile App)

## Purpose

This is the application the user installs on their phone.

It will display:

* Login
* Dashboard
* Upload Report
* AI Analysis
* History
* Compare Reports

### Why Flutter?

✅ One codebase

Instead of writing:

* Android App
* iPhone App

We write one application.

Advantages:

* Faster development
* Large community
* Good performance
* Easy to maintain

---

# 2. FastAPI (Backend)

Flutter talks to FastAPI.

Example:

User presses:

```text
Upload Report
```

Flutter sends the report to FastAPI.

FastAPI then:

* Saves the file
* Calls OCR
* Calls AI
* Stores results
* Sends everything back

Think of FastAPI as the manager of the app.

---

# 3. PostgreSQL (Database)

Purpose:

Store structured information.

Examples:

* Users
* Reports
* Blood values
* AI analyses

It should **not** store the PDF itself.

---

# 4. AWS S3 (Cloud Storage)

Large files belong here.

Examples:

* PDF reports
* Images
* Future exports

Advantages:

* Reliable
* Scalable
* Low cost for beginners

---

# 5. Google Cloud Vision OCR

Purpose:

Read text from uploaded reports.

Input:

```text
Blood Report PDF
```

Output:

```text
Hemoglobin : 13.4

HbA1c : 5.7

Vitamin D : 26
```

This removes the need for manual typing.

---

# 6. OpenAI API

Purpose:

Convert medical values into plain-language explanations.

Instead of:

```text
HbA1c : 6.8
```

The app can say:

> "Your HbA1c is higher than the normal range, suggesting elevated average blood sugar over the past few months. Please discuss these results with your healthcare provider."

This makes the app useful even for people who don't understand medical terminology.

---

# How They Work Together

```text
User
   │
   ▼
Flutter App
   │
   ▼
FastAPI Backend
   │
   ├── Save PDF → AWS S3
   │
   ├── Extract Text → OCR
   │
   ├── Generate Explanation → OpenAI
   │
   └── Save Results → PostgreSQL
```

Each service performs one task well.

---

# Why Not Build Everything Ourselves?

You asked an excellent question a few days ago:

> "Can we skip writing everything ourselves and use open-source code?"

The answer is **yes**, and that's exactly what we're planning.

For example:

* We won't build an OCR engine—we'll use an existing service.
* We won't train our own AI model—we'll use the OpenAI API.
* We won't build a cloud storage system—we'll use AWS S3.
* We won't write our own database engine—we'll use PostgreSQL.

This lets us focus on **creating a great product** instead of reinventing technology that already exists.

---

