# 👨‍🏫 Mentor's Note

This is an important mindset shift.

A few weeks ago, you were trying to learn every programming concept. Today, you're learning **how to assemble a real product** using proven technologies.

That's much closer to how many startups work. Teams don't create their own database, OCR engine, cloud storage, or AI model—they integrate trusted services and focus on delivering value to users.

One improvement I'd make to our plan is to keep everything **modular**. If, in the future, you decide to switch from Google Cloud Vision to another OCR service, or from one AI provider to another, the rest of the app should continue working with minimal changes. Designing with that flexibility in mind from the beginning will make the app easier to maintain and grow.
